Why this could matter now

The policy environment is unusually aligned for a tool like this. The FTC’s 2025 surveillance-pricing study said firms were using a wide range of personal data for individualized pricing, and the CFPB has been pushing on data-broker and sensitive-data practices that can feed those systems.  ￼

So the wedge is strong:
	•	consumers already hate unfair hidden pricing
	•	regulators are already scrutinizing surveillance pricing
	•	merchants may want a way to prove clean behavior
	•	AI makes both the abuse and the defense easier

